<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Eutrombicula helleri (Oudemans, 1911). A—scutum and eyes (specimen ZIN 9103, Paraguay), B—scutum and eyes (specimen ZIN 8841, Peru), C—ventral aspect of idiosoma (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru), D—dorsal aspect of idiosoma (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru), E—humeral seta (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru), F—dorsal idiosomal seta (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru), G—ventral idiosomal seta (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru), H—dorsal aspect of gnathosoma (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru), I—ventral aspect of gnathosoma (specimen ZIN 8852, Peru). Abbreviations as in Fig. 2. Scale bars: 50 µm (A, B), 100 µm (C, D), 20 µm (E–I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6598100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598102>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Eutrombicula helleri (Oudemans, 1911), specimen ZIN 8852, Peru. A—leg I (trochanter–tarsus), B—leg II (trochanter–tarsus), C—leg III (trochanter–tarsus). Abbreviations as in Fig. 3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6598102/files/figure.png" ;
